						               													<description>Tryangles is a space-themed game having a board with a triangular grid containing a few black holes, planets, stars etc, with a Base area for each player. Each player has a set of triangle-based polyominoes containing 2, 3 or 4 spaces. A die is thrown to indicate whether a player may place a piece with 2, 3 or 4 spaces. Players place pieces over the special areas of the board with the constraints that:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     the player must first play in their base and all further plays must attach by at least two sides to pieces already on the board&amp;#10;     black holes may not be played on&amp;#10;     planets and stars must be fully occupied with one placement. Planets score 10 points and the sun scores 30 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player to score the most points wins, though the rules do not specify a game end condition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
